# Provider Adapters (LLM/GenAI integrations)

- All external model calls go through /src/providers/* adapters.
- No provider-specific logic inside core domain or UI components.
- Adapters must:
  - accept typed requests (task + inputs + candidate prompt)
  - return typed responses (output + metadata + cost/latency if available)
  - implement retries with exponential backoff for transient errors
  - support request id / trace id propagation

Provider config:
- Must be read from env vars only (never hardcode keys).
- Support switching provider/model without code changes where possible.

Batching:
- When generating N candidates, prefer a single "generate candidates" call if provider supports it;
  otherwise parallelize with safe concurrency limits.
